\begin_layout Subsection
Regulator's final period offer
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
At time 
\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

, the regulator has observed a parcel specific signal of environmental value
 
\begin_inset Formula $\se_{i}$
\end_inset

 and knows the mean environmental service value 
\begin_inset Formula $\meanE$
\end_inset

.
 The true environmental service value provided by the parcel is 
\begin_inset Formula $\env_{i}=\meanE+\se_{i}+\re_{i}$
\end_inset

 where 
\begin_inset Formula $\re$
\end_inset

 is a mean 0 deviation from the expected value given the information available.
 The regulator knows the overall mean private development externality value
 
\begin_inset Formula $\meanP$
\end_inset

 and the public development value 
\begin_inset Formula $\pub_{i}$
\end_inset

, but does not know the value of a private deviation 
\begin_inset Formula $\rp_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 The landowner knows the value of this deviation and thus knows the value
 of her land is 
\begin_inset Formula $\meanP+\pub_{i}+\rp_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 Let 
\begin_inset Formula $\left[\begin{array}{c}
\se_{i}\\
\re_{i}\\
\rp_{i}
\end{array}\right]\sim N_{3}\left(\mathbf{0},\mathbf{\Sigma}\right)$
\end_inset

 where the variance-covariance matrix has the form
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\mathbf{\Sigma}=\left[\begin{array}{ccc}
\sigma_{\se}^{2} & 0 & \sigma_{\se\rp}\\
0 & \sigma_{\re}^{2} & \sigma_{\re\rp}\\
\sigma_{\se\rp} & \sigma_{\re\rp} & \sigma_{\rp}^{2}
\end{array}\right].
\]

\end_inset

Based on previous offers and information, the regulator infers that there
 is an upper bound (
\begin_inset Formula $\ubPriv$
\end_inset

) for the private development value of land that has not yet been converted.
 Mathematically, this implies that for any parcel that has not been converted
 
\begin_inset Formula $\priv_{i}\leq\ubPriv$
\end_inset

, which implies that 
\begin_inset Formula $\rp_{i}\leq\ubRpi=\ubPriv-\pub_{i}-\meanP$
\end_inset

.
 From the regulator's perspective, the distribution of 
\begin_inset Formula $\rp_{i}$
\end_inset

 conditional on the inferred value 
\begin_inset Formula $\ubPriv$
\end_inset

 and the observed signal 
\begin_inset Formula $\se_{i}$
\end_inset

 is given by
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
f_{\rp_{i}|\ubPriv,\se_{i}}\left(\rp|\ubPriv,\se_{i}\right)=\begin{cases}
\frac{f_{\rp|\se_{i}}\left(\rp|\se_{i}\right)}{F_{\rp|\se_{i}}\left(\ubRpi|\se_{i}\right)} & \mbox{ if }\rp_{i}\leq\ubRpi=\ubPriv-\pub_{i}-\meanP\\
0 & \mbox{ otherwise.}
\end{cases}
\]

\end_inset

Since this is the last period, the landowner will accept the offer if 
\begin_inset Formula $\priv_{i}\leq\offer_{i}$
\end_inset

 or if 
\begin_inset Formula $\rp_{i}\leq\offer_{i}-\meanP-\pub_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 The regulator is uncertain about the values of both 
\begin_inset Formula $\rp_{i}$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $\re_{i}$
\end_inset

.
 The realized value of 
\begin_inset Formula $\rp_{i}$
\end_inset

 determines whether the parcel will be conserved or not and the realized
 value of 
\begin_inset Formula $\re_{i}$
\end_inset

 determines the actual benefit the regulator receives if the parcel is conserved.
 We can thus write the regulator's expected payoff
