\begin_layout Standard
Since 
\begin_inset Formula $f_{N}\left(\cdot\right)$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $F_{N}\left(\cdot\right)$
\end_inset

 are strictly positive everywhere, this expression only has a solution if
 
\begin_inset Formula 
\[
\frac{1}{\sigma_{\priv|\se,\pub}}\left(\meanE+\se_{i}+\offer_{i}\left(\frac{\sigma_{\re\rp}}{\sigma_{\priv|\se,\pub}}-1\right)-\pub_{i}-\mu_{\priv|\se,\pub}\frac{\sigma_{\re\rp}}{\sigma_{\priv|\se,\pub}}\right)>0
\]

